  "doc_id": "10734",
  "text": "Our previous work described that DPI, which blocks ROS generation through its inhibitory effects on flavoprotein-containing enzymes, blocked HIF-1␣ accumulation during Ang II treatment. We suggested this was mediated through the inhibition of the NADPH oxidase. Not surprisingly, it has been reported that DPI is not a specific NADPH oxidase inhibitor [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Moreover, DPI inhibits all flavin-containing enzymes, including those found in the mitochondria [CITATION_3] . Here, our work shows that DPI does indeed block mtROS generation in VSMCs during Ang II treatment and indicates that DPI blocks HIF-1␣ stabilization by Ang II.",
